# Shared-By-Default Architecture

There are **exactly 2 execution contexts** for game rules:

1. **Offline** ‚Äî Client runs the engine locally (Single Player, Tournament vs AI, Bust vs AI). Uses `lib/core/models/offline_game_engine.dart` which exports `lib/shared/engine/game_engine.dart`.
2. **Online** ‚Äî Server runs the engine (`server/lib/game_session.dart`) and imports the same `lib/shared/engine/game_engine.dart`.

Tournament and Bust are **session types**, not separate engines. They orchestrate rounds via `TableScreen` and the shared engine. No parallel game-logic implementations.

## Where New Code Goes

| What | Where |
|---|---|
| New card rule / game mechanic | `lib/shared/engine/game_engine.dart` ‚Äî `_applySpecialEffect`, `validatePlay`, or a new shared function |
| New win/loss condition | `lib/shared/rules/win_condition_rules.dart` |
| New penalty/chain rule | `lib/shared/rules/pickup_chain_rules.dart` |
| Mode-specific setup (deck, hand size, round config) | A config object passed as a parameter to `TableScreen`, NOT a new parallel screen |
| Bust-specific meta-game (rounds, elimination) | `lib/features/bust/` ‚Äî orchestrates `TableScreen`, does not reimplement it |
| New UI screen | Only justified if the UI is genuinely different (e.g. `BustEliminationScreen`), never for different game logic |

## Server Sync (When It's Needed)

The server already calls `validatePlay`, `applyPlay`, and `applyDraw` from the shared engine. **Internal changes to those functions propagate automatically** ‚Äî no changes to `server/lib/game_session.dart` needed.

Update `server/lib/game_session.dart` only when the **engine API changes** (e.g. new parameters to `validatePlay`, new function to call, different return shape). After any engine change, redeploy the server so it runs the updated code.

## Test Both Contexts

Always verify game logic works in **both offline and online**:

- **Offline** ‚Äî Add or extend unit tests in `test/engine_test.dart` (or `test/*_test.dart`) that call `validatePlay`, `applyPlay`, `applyDraw` directly. These cover the shared engine used by the client.
- **Online** ‚Äî For logic exercised by the server, add tests in `server/test/` that drive `GameSession` (e.g. via `seedStateForTesting` + play_cards messages) or that import the shared engine and assert on `validatePlay`/`applyPlay` outcomes. The server uses the same engine, so shared-engine unit tests cover both; add server/integration tests when the flow involves `GameSession` handling (protocol, turn timer, broadcasts).

Never ship a rule or engine fix without tests that would catch regressions in both offline play and online play.

## Anti-Patterns to Reject

```dart
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî parallel screen that reimplements game loop
class NewModeGameScreen extends StatefulWidget {
  // 1000+ lines duplicating validatePlay, applyPlay, AI scheduling...
}

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî thin coordinator that configures TableScreen
class NewModeCoordinator extends StatelessWidget {
  Widget build(BuildContext context) => TableScreen(
    newModeConfig: NewModeConfig(...),
    onRoundComplete: _handleRoundComplete,
  );
}
```

```dart
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî rule only in offline/client code
void _applySpecialEffect(...) {
  // new card effect only here
}

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî rule in shared engine, consumed by both offline and server
// lib/shared/engine/game_engine.dart
GameState _applySpecialEffect(GameState gs, CardModel card, ...) {
  case Rank.newCard:
    return gs.copyWith(newEffect: ...);
}
// server/lib/game_session.dart already calls applyPlay() ‚Üí picks it up automatically
```

## Checklist for Any New Feature

- [ ] Game logic added to `lib/shared/engine/game_engine.dart` (not a feature folder)
- [ ] `server/lib/game_session.dart` updated **only if** engine API changed (new params, new functions)
- [ ] `test/engine_test.dart` has tests covering the new logic
- [ ] Logic verified for **both** offline and online (see Test Both Contexts above)
- [ ] No new parallel game screen created (use `TableScreen` with a config param)
- [ ] `docs/rules-by-mode.md` updated if the rule affects gameplay
